Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner sausages
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 are overweight, where overweight affects 9% of the school population and obesity 5%.
Obese children come mostly from families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to current research.
It demonstrates again the importance of the environment where you grow for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
At the table, obsessed children eat, for example, sausages at least twice as often as children from normal-weight families.
For dinner, more than 19% of obese people had eaten fries the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence."
In families of overweight children there is no practice of sports, which is applicable to most families today, where only 15% of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of last school year and involved almost 900 basic education children from all over the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the program "Obesity is not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the company Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from 4th to 8th grade.
A proper diet and plenty of exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly reduce the number of children who are overweight and even obese.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five meals per day according to the regimen: breakfast, lunch, lunch, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," one of the survey results said.
No breakfast but with sausage for dinner
The specialists warn that, in a healthy development, are important, in addition, the details, which also count, such as having a fixed time for breakfast in the family.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of school families eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast on their own.
But the worst thing was to discover that in 10% of households nothing is eaten for breakfast.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that in families of obese children, insane chips are consumed much more often.
Almost everyone – regardless of weight – drinks sweet soft drinks daily (70%).
As a general rule, more than 40% of the children surveyed do sport, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study made it possible for the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all the possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The dietary preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15, from the point of view of healthy eating, are far from ideal."
Among his favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
“The popularity of sweet soft drinks is especially alarming,” the study’s final report warns.
The main meal is the palm, the pasta, followed closely by the poultry.
Practically, children always reject legumes and the taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Changing to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive the right information.
“In the control group of study participants, who completed the questionnaire after completing the ‘Obesity is not a coincidence’ prevention program, there was in many cases an important change in favor of the principles of healthy eating,” the study’s results show.
It is interesting, for example, about soft drinks, where many children would start to prefer normal water.
Children would also choose more frequently in the questionnaire poultry and fish for the main meal and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
