The stylist must have a global vision.
The three invited specialists animated the conference on Saturday with information on all types of bodies.
The stylist Honza Pokorn<0xC3><0xBD>, the fashion designer Jakub Polanka and the fashion photographer Ben Ren<0xC4><0x8D>.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should know how to take advantage of this.
And a good stylist knows how to work with the same garment in different ways.
Variability is fundamental in this case.
Thus, such a gabardine (or as they say in English, trench-coat) can be dressed to the classic with jeans and t-shirt, but it also serves to dress the naked body in heels and photograph it as if it were actually a dress.
Or just roll up your sleeves and raise your neck to get a totally different image.
“Play with it,” he insisted.
