In order not to stay in passive listening and put something into practice, we have learned to cover the sole of the shoes.
Even during photo shoots in the studio, on a flat surface, you could damage the sole and even more the outside.
And we did nothing but clothe and clothe.
We could not touch the shoes with scissors so as not to damage them by accident.
So you had to be very skilled.
Mario has given me a joy in praising my work unreservedly.
The truth is, I'm not very good at those skills.
This is just a small part of everything we’ve heard throughout the weekend, in the second part of the course.
I have already realized that dedicating myself to styling at a professional level is not a road of roses, but I do not care exactly what people say.
In Need for Speed: The Run you compete across America.
Reviewed
A trip, in principle carefree, is complicated by a series of improper carelessnesses of a routine trip during tomorrow’s shift.
To a certain extent, the expectations were met, but this was of no use if, in reality, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new installment, which is added to the title The Run, aroused great expectations already before its premiere.
He promised that he would give new airs to the old racing saga Need for Speed and, as a result of what was shown, it appears as a game that should not end up being a simple action genre again.
We are also curious to know how the inserted scenes would look, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As is often the case in the NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in the total count points are lost due to absurd failures, which have been appearing in the series for years.
In reality they cannot even be called errors, but it is rather the incomprehensible dislike of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco, and your mission is to get to New York first.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then over fifty races.
From this it follows that each race takes place by a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
In this way, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous deliveries of the series.
Therefore, it is nothing from the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
Thus, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you have to be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that’s enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a required number of rivals (normal in a classic race), then you try to gain time (timed classic duel) and then a duel awaits you against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this appears sometimes the police, which does nothing but make things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than you would expect (specifically, there are only three).
But the end result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the context already mentioned, is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of the previous episodes.
That means that it is no longer a big deal, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you’re looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a race conceived with a lot of action is well suited to this style of driving, although we can find something better among the competition games.
So far, everything in order.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, collisions are no longer the same.
From games of this type you can not expect to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a hit against any object, you can not predict how your car will react, with which everything is not in order.
It is typical that, when doing a very tight overtaking or circulating the car with normal traffic, there are only slight frictions, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or even completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or leave the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each race only five resets are available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it is nothing more than a help in case something goes wrong, but it is not very trustworthy.
Sometimes, even resetting does not help, it only helps to learn the given stage by heart.
A major disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes you angry especially in situations, when you see that two cars that meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or brake.
It is the same when you arrive, because it is programmed because the “surprise” will always happen before your noses.
Adversaries also have an advantage.
Throughout the game you will arrive at places where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always overtake you in the same place.
In addition this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming in front of you, so at first you can muffle the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that you will surely be disappointed right away.
And it’s a shame, because even though the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and action-packed, so it’s often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn’t matter, whether the merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or the ranking in the race so it doesn’t fit the boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is to change cars during races.
You have to be aware of the gasoline supplies next to the road, because precisely there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will have enough what you have.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and exotic super sports cars for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain roads.
In addition main narrative thread also appears a parallel challenge thread, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know by the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver is given several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community features.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you get to the subway tunnel (pass), where you start running in the dark on the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, the metro convoy arrives behind you and takes you in front without further ado.
In the writing we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one thought even a little or if the authors really take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects are in most cases pleasant, sometimes even superb.
What a pity that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This especially affects accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the "each of his father and mother" category, but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for their music.
The final feel of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It feels like the game is not over.
The fun is guaranteed, but be prepared because the mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the force of airport reflectors.
The choirs of the Carolina University will participate in the concert "Students of Velvet".
The joint celebration of International Student Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
Twenty choirs from high school and university centers will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"Universidad Carolina has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the festival committee is the rector Václav Hampl," said the head of the organization, Jakub <0xC4><0x8C>aloun.
