This was the work of the Caleño who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A lophoscopist from Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is key.
On November 4, a lophoscopist from the CTI of Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the identity of the top leader of the FARC: "Alfonso Cano", through the comparison of his fingerprints.
Of the seven lofoscopists who work in the section of the CTI, that week was the turn of "availability" to Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the area of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, Gonzalez worked in municipalities of Chocó, where he often had to stay for more than five days in the jungle to reach the site where the corpses were to be identified.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after taking the corresponding courses, specialized in lophoscopy, which is the study of the skin of friction, that is, the palms of the hands and feet.
The week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano to Eliazar warned him to wear clothes minimum for three days.
Something big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for Cauca in a helicopter from Palmyra.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected of being the man who led the world’s oldest guerrilla, so they asked him to carry Guillermo León Sáenz’s decadal card (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the research team at the site where the corpse was, he did not recognize it by its physical appearance, as it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was beardless, dressed like a local peasant, without glasses and much thinner.
But the footprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a transplanter and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse to those of the card.
His eye did not fail him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was in charge of confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón, that he was the top leader of the FARC.
In Search of the Footprint
For a dactylographer of the Sijín de Cali the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliazar González, in the press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don’t know our work.
Fingerprinting is an exact science, with no margin for error, that can become key in resolving crimes.
In addition to identifying bodies, lophoscopists support investigations into crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identities of captured people.
When captured, many criminals present false ballots or have no papers.
We take their fingerprints and look them up in the database.
The investigator said that, in a case of theft, it was up to him to remove a piece of wall from a house, because in that place the thief had supported his hand to take out a safe full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to make a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to get the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different thefts," he recalled.
Fingerprints can also rule out or reaffirm suspects in homicide cases.
They recently found a dead man, with bottles of liquor around him.
Through the investigation it was determined that a relative could be suspected of the crime and, indeed, a fingerprint on the bottle coincided.
Although this does not guarantee that he was the killer, it does place him at the crime scene.
A CTI fingerprinter explained that in the objects "the fingerprints are taken with chemical or physical reagents."
When they appear, a transplanter or ribbon is used to lift them.
After this, the impressions are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
“The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians,” the CTI expert said.
He clarified that not everything is as shown on the CSI TV show.
Just as not everything that shines is gold, not everything that is touched becomes imprint.
However, if it can be used, if the respective comparison is made.
